items.description: This study presents a machine learning framework designed to predict employee promotion outcomes based on various performance metrics and demographic factors. Including performance reviews, tenure, skill assessments, and training participation, we developed a predictive model using algorithms such as Random Forest, and Decision Tree etc,.

This ontology provides researchers, developers, and practitioners with a unified, machine-readable framework to guide the design and assessment of fair ML systems.

items.description: A Machine Learning framework simulating biochar-assisted soil bioremediation and crop productivity. Predicts heavy metal removal and nitrogen use efficiency by modeling physicochemical adsorption, microbial synergy, and partial root-zone drying effects.

items.description: Cyber Shield is an AI-driven cybersecurity framework that detects network intrusions, phishing emails, and insider threats using machine learning models. items.name: Nanofluid-HTC-ML
items.description: This project implements a machine learning-based framework for predicting the convective Heat Transfer Coefficient (HTC) of nanofluids by analyzing the complex interaction between the dispersed solid phase and continuous liquid phase. The selected model achieves an R2 Score of 0.9826 and a RMSE of 425.98 W/m2K.

Built upon the high-performance FastAPI framework, it provides a responsive REST API that can easily integrate with web or mobile frontends.

items.description: A comprehensive machine learning pipeline for seizure detection and classification using pose-based video analysis. items.name: Probabilistic-Agentic-bitcoin-with-ML-
items.description: A Python-based framework designed to quantify risk in Bitcoin trading using Probabilistic Machine Learning. Most ML models fail in crypto because they ignore oratorical uncertainty (the inherent randomness of the market). This repo provides tools to build models that don't just predict the next move

items.name: Dharshan_Portfolio
items.description: Today, I explored how to build interactive AI applications using the Gradio framework  a powerful tool that allows you to create simple, shareable web interfaces for your machine learning and Generative AI models.

items.name: Erhai-Data-Analysis
items.description: Code for the integrated feature selection in the manuscript entitled "Leveraging Niche Divergence for Early Detection of Cyanobacterial Blooms: A Metagenomics and Machine Learning Framework".

items.name: XAI
items.description: Explainable AI (XAI) framework designed to provide transparent, interpretable insights for both tabular and image-based machine learning models.

items.name: miglan
items.description: Framework for Data Science and Machine Learning

items.name: portfolio
items.description: I'm a Results-driven Software Engineer with expertise in computer vision and machine learning applications. My journey in tech has been fueled by a passion for creating intelligent systems that solve real-world problems.  With a strong background in Python programming, deep learning frameworks, and image processing technologies.

items.name: passive-dns-ml-evaluation
items.description: Passive DNS threat detection using lexical machine learning techniques. This repository contains a reproducible research prototype and experimental evaluation framework for assessing the feasibility, accuracy, and performance of machine-learning-based malicious domain detection in a passive DNS monitoring context.

items.name: Factor-Mining-Framework
items.description: This project implements a complete quantitative research pipeline for mining, combining, and evaluating alpha factors. It covers the entire lifecycle from data simulation and feature engineering to machine learning optimization (Elastic Net) and rigorous performance testing (Quantile Backtesting, IC Analysis, and Factor Decay).

items.name: ML-Framework-for-Depression-Risk-Stratification
items.description: A Machine Learning Framework for Depression Risk Stratification Among University Students: Integrating Predictive Performance with Dual Interpretability Techniques

items.name: XAI-for-Solar-Electrolysis-Green-Hydrogen-Production-and-Yield-Optimization
items.description: Reproducible framework for forecasting and optimizing green hydrogen production from solar-powered electrolysis using physics-informed feature engineering, interpretable machine learning (SHAP/LIME), and scenario analysis. Includes public data pipeline, Python notebooks, figures, and LaTeX tables for full transparency.

items.name: Feasibility-Aware-ML-Energy-Materials
items.description: Feasibility-aware analysis of latent representations learned by multitask machine-learning models for electrochemical energy materials. The framework reveals domain structure, transferability limits, and data-supported performance regimes across porous carbons and MOFs.

items.name: physics-informed-bandgap-ml-2d-materials
items.description: A physics-informed machine learning framework for predicting electronic bandgaps of two-dimensional materials, with a focused application to transition-metal dichalcogenides (TMDCs).

items.name: Deforestation-and-Vegetation-Loss-Monitoring-in-Southern-Nigeria-Using-Remote-Sensing-and-ML
items.description: AI-driven framework for monitoring deforestation and vegetation loss in Southern Nigeria using synthetic remote sensing data and machine learning. Designed for reproducibility, policy simulation, and capacity building in data-scarce regions, with scalable pathways to real satellite-based forest monitoring systems.

items.name: BeyondTheAbyss_SARS2
items.description: Integrated multi-scale computational framework for SARS-CoV-2 RBD variant analysis. Combines homology modeling, molecular     dynamics (GROMACS), MM-PBSA binding energetics, and machine learning to predict ACE2/CD147 receptor affinity and immune       escape across 31 variants.

items.name: ga-inverse-design-double-perovskites
items.description: Genetic algorithmbased inverse design framework for discovering double perovskite oxides with target band gaps for photovoltaic applications. Integrates DFT-informed machine learning as a fast surrogate and validates top candidates using first-principles DFT calculations.

items.name: dasf-core
items.description: Framework for computing Machine Learning algorithms in Python using Dask and RAPIDS AI.

items.name: Java-Machine-Learning
items.description: Framework de Machine Learning en Java avec implmentation de rgression linaire, KNN (classification/rgression), prtraitement des donnes et mtriques d'valuation.

items.name: Master_Thesis
items.description: Development of an Explainable Machine Learning Framework for Intelligent Train Operation

items.name: Global-Food-Waste-A-Predictive-Modeling-Approach
items.description: This project developed a robust machine learning framework to forecast annual global food waste volume (in metric tons) using macroeconomic and demographic data.

items.name: Validation_framework_for_imputation
items.description: Available code and database for Decision-Making Criteria on Choosing Appropriate Imputation Methods for Incomplete Datasets Prepared for Machine Learning

items.name: benfluc.github.io
items.description: My portfolio showcases projects in data analysis and data science, with emphasis on statistical analysis, machine learning models, and applied analytics. I develop data-driven solutions using Python and analytical frameworks, focusing on reliability, interpretability, and real-world applicability across different domains.

items.name: nnpdf
items.description: An open-source machine learning framework for global analyses of parton distributions.

items.name: Zero-Forcing-Set-GML
items.description: Reference implementation for A Graph Machine Learning Framework to Compute Zero Forcing Sets in Graphs. Includes GNN-based models, greedy baselines, and evaluation pipelines for computing zero forcing sets efficiently on large graphs.

items.name: creditbyte-fraud-detection
items.description: A machine learning project handling class imbalances and cost-sensitive learning towards improving fraud detection frameworks. In fulfillment of ML3301.

items.name: folax
items.description: Folax (Finite Operator Learning with JAX) is a framework for solving and optimizing PDEs by integrating machine learning with numerical methods in computational mechanics.

items.name: FusedSCEquiTensorPot
items.description: A Multi-Operator Equivariant Framework for High-Fidelity Machine Learning Force Fields

items.name: Tensorflow-Project
items.description: TensorFlow is an open-source deep learning framework developed by Google. It helps build, train, and deploy machine-learning models using tensors and data-flow graphs. TensorFlow supports neural networks, GPU/TPU acceleration, automatic differentiation, and is widely used in AI applications like image recognition and NLP

items.name: linfa
items.description: A Rust machine learning framework.

items.name: Tensorflow-
items.description: TensorFlow is an open-source deep learning framework developed by Google. It helps build, train, and deploy machine-learning models using tensors and data-flow graphs. TensorFlow supports neural networks, GPU/TPU acceleration, automatic differentiation, and is widely used in AI applications like image recognition and NLP.

items.name: LNN4ACP
items.description: LNN4ACP is a novel stacked framework that integrates both machine learning and deep learning components for accurate ACP identification and virtual generation.

items.name: ML-and-Deep-Learning-Projects-and-practice
items.description: multiple machine learning and deep learning practice projects and framework practice repo

items.name: SAFER-6G-Project
items.description: SAFER-6G : Framework IA pour la scurit des rseaux 6G. Le projet utilise le Machine Learning pour analyser le trafic rseau simul, dtecter les cyberattaques en temps rel (dbit, latence, etc.), et prsenter les alertes sur un tableau de bord interactif.

items.name: smallml
items.description: SmallML is a three-layer Bayesian framework that enables small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) to build production-grade machine learning models despite having limited customer data.

items.name: pybroker
items.description: Algorithmic Trading in Python with Machine Learning

items.name: coevolutionary-episteme
items.description: A machine learning framework, dataset and research sub-module about coevolutionary planetary intelligence dynamics. This project explores how nurturing its emergent patterns may lead to a synergistic increase in the overall capability and intelligence of both individual agents and the collective system.

items.name: Data-Science-Portfolio
items.description: A collection of comprehensive data science projects that demonstrate practical skills in data analysis, machine learning, deep learning, NLP, SQL & NoSQL databases, big data frameworks, AWS tools, and real-world business problem solving. This portfolio highlights the full workflow of data science.

items.name: Quantum-Fraud-Detection
items.description: A novel hybrid quantumclassical machine learning framework designed to enhance the detection of collusive merchant fraud in financial systems.

items.name: Football-Predictor
items.description: A sophisticated machine learning framework for predicting football match outcomes using ELO ratings, statistical modeling, and hybrid feature engineering.

items.name: Statistical-Time-Series-Drift-Analysis-Framework
items.description: Built a statistical analysis framework to identify behavioral changes in time-series data without using machine learning. The system compares data across temporal windows using descriptive statistics and distribution measures to detect drift, producing clear and explainable summaries of when and how data patterns change.

items.name: tourism-data-analysis
items.description: This project presents a robust analytics framework for evaluating tourism performance across India. Through KPIs, machine learning models, and interactive visualizations.  The project enhances Indias potential to boost domestic and international tourism sustainably and effectively.

items.name: Ai-chatbot
items.description: A simple rule-based AI chatbot built using pure Python (Python 3.14.2 compatible) without any external libraries or machine learning frameworks. The chatbot uses pattern matching and decision rules to simulate intelligent conversation, making it ideal for learning the fundamentals of Artificial Intelligence, NLP basics, and Python programming.

items.name: HydroSoil-AI
items.description: Physics-Informed Machine Learning framework for global Soil Hydraulic Conductivity (Ksat) prediction using Adams' Compaction and Shin's Pore Geometry models.

items.name: NRLMF-DTI-MurrayaBAT
items.description: NRLMF-DTI-MurrayaBAT is a drugtarget interaction framework that applies NRLMF-based negative inference to address data imbalance and employs supervised machine learning to predict interactions between Murraya paniculata bioactive compounds and brown adipose tissueassociated proteins in obesity-related conditions.

items.name: Java-ML-Framework
items.description: Mini-framework de Machine Learning en Java inspir de Scikit-Learn. Implmente Rgression Linaire, KNN, Scalers et train/test split.

items.name: aurora
items.description: Open Machine Learning Compiler Framework

items.name: PRISM
items.description: Machine learning framework for predicting chronic disease onset and analyzing multimorbidity networks using CHARLS longitudinal data.

items.name: Harmful-Algal-Bloom-Prediction-in-Niger-Delta-Coastal-Waters-Using-Remote-Sensing-and-ML
items.description: Machine learningdriven prediction of harmful algal blooms in Niger Delta coastal waters using synthetic remote sensing and water quality data, demonstrating an early warning framework for coastal ecosystem monitoring, environmental risk assessment, and decision support in data-scarce regions.

items.name: SIRT1_ML_NPASS
items.description: An integrative machine learning, explainable AI, and molecular simulation framework for the discovery of selective SIRT1 inhibitors against Triple Negative Breast Cancer

items.name: Sales-Marketing-Analytics-Data-Driven-Customer-Intelligence
items.description: Developed a 9-module analytics framework leveraging data analysis, machine learning and statistical modeling. Understand: Revenue Analysis , Cohort Retention, RFM Segmentation; Predict: Churn Prediction, LTV Prediction , Sales Forecasting , Next Purchase Day ; Optimise: Market Response, Uplift Modeling ,  A/B Testing

items.description: Python Fast Dataflow programming  framework for Data pipeline work( Web Crawler,Machine Learning,Quantitative Trading.etc)
